    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Summer Squall in Southampton</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Isabella Montgomery letter on May 30 article on complaints of Southampton summer residents deplores fact that Washington, DC, residents pay federal taxes without federal representation</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Summer Residents Want Year-Round Voice'' (front page, May 30):</p>
        <p>There is a striking parallel between the situation of Southampton's summer residents and residents of our nation's capital.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Summer Residents Want Year-Round Voice'' (front page, May 30):</p>
        <p>There is a striking parallel between the situation of Southampton's summer residents and residents of our nation's capital.</p>
        <p>Homeowners in Southampton are objecting to taxation without representation, a founding principle of our country. Washington residents have always paid federal taxes without the privilege of federal representation.</p>
        <p>Can we hope that any success for well-to-do property owners in Southampton might bring relief for citizens of Washington?</p>
        <p>ISABELLA MONTGOMERY  Washington, May 31, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
